  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl02_LabelType\">You have a strong emotional attachment to a person or object that you&rsquo;re terrified of losing.</span></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Effects</strong></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl02_LabelType\">The GM chooses the object of your attachment. Whenever the object of your attachment is either threatened, in danger, or in someone else&rsquo;s possession, you take a &ndash;1 penalty on Will saves and a &ndash;2 penalty on saves against fear effects. If the person or object to which you&rsquo;re attached is ever lost, killed, or destroyed, exchange this drawback for the Doubt drawback.</span></p>",
